name: De Umah Bali Eco Tradi Home
address: Br. undisan kaja, H95W+RVF, Jl. Raya Undisan, Undisan, Kec. Tembuku, Kabupaten Bangli, Bali 80671, Indonesia
review 1:
Really nice retreat from the chaos of city life and packed tourist areas of Bali.
Here they have meals, spa, laundry services, comfortable lodges, a bar, and swimming pools. It felt like a solitude village in nature.

Note: arriving and leaving is a challenge. If you call Grab be prepared to tip or pay by cash. You may pay the lodging to drive you but they'll charge more than Grab.
review 2: The place is beautiful. The service supposed to be outstanding  but the truth is often under the expectations. No warm water, stinky rooms, old scooters to rent, and an small things, which mkde us sligjtly disappointed.
review 3:
We’re a filming Crew and stayed here for work. For us the Place was very nice with a charming Atmosphere. We loved our Little Houses, the Pool and the Restaurant. You feel like living in the Nature and we had no Problems with the Sounds of the Temple around.
Only Thing: if you stay here you need a Driver or a Bike to go around. But for a few Days „pass through“ it is the Perfect Place to get new Energy and chill a bit in a nice Atmosphere.
We loved the Breakfast and the Restaurant in generell. The Staff is very friendly and warm from their Hearts.
review 4: Amazing Place. Very nice Rooms and attentive stuff. Beautiful Garden und very good food in the restaurant. The place also has a bar. In the located in the middle of some really cool waterfalls. So if you have the chance for a stopover driving North to South, or vice versa and take it slow, you can stay a night here. We highly recommend this place to our friends.
review 5: I liked the place very much. Very nice service, large rooms with nice wooden furniture. Simple, but good breakfast. On the down side is slow internet, but as it is remote area I believe the owner can  ot do much about this issue. We had a good realx there. Recommend!
